There is some data from CERN [5] which disagrees with the sign of this prediction, but the

%
disagreement is not statistically significant. A precise measurement of g in E semileptonic decay
V


would determine the magnitude of N.

An easier measurement [1,6] is the ratio of semileptonic decay rates for E+ %
and E where


' E% 6 7 ¯e<
